Lagos State governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, on Monday, signed the stateâ€™s 2019 Appropriation Bill into law. The Lagos 2019 budget which totals N873,532,460,725 consists of N479, 691,705 for capital expenditures and N393,841,387 for recurrent expenditures. The capital expense takes up 45% of the budget while recurrent expense takes up 55% of the budget. The budget signed by Sanwo-Olu was N21 bn higher than the budget proposed by ex-governor, Akinwunmi Ambode. The former governor proposed a budget of N852,316,936,483 to the State House of Assembly on February 5, 2019.
